  <body class="web-os-back">
    <div>
      <h1 class="boot-title-oobe">What type of install do you want?</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="selection-box">
      <div class="selection-box-box">
        <h3 class="selection-box-h3"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-cog"></span> Standard (Recommended)</h3>
        <div class="selection-sub">
          <p>
            Web-OS will automatically install bower, mocha, nodemon, less and sass, install the modules (shown in package.json and bower.json),
            configure Web-OS and apply the dashboard. Recommended for people with only one web-app in development, which is writen in Nodejs.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="selection-box">
      <div class="selection-box-box">
        <h3 class="selection-box-h3"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-cog"></span> Instances</h3>
        <div class="selection-sub">
          <p>
            We will install common web-app development tools (<b>Ruby on Rails</b>, <b>gem</b>, <b>rvm</b>, <b>bundle</b>,
            <b>Nodejs express-generator</b>,
            <b>npm</b>, <b>apache maven</b> ) and runtimes (<b>java sdk, java jre, nodejs, iojs, python 2 or 3</b>).
            To add to this, you will be able to use the web-os dashboard to manage, create and deploy multiple web-apps (instances), store
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
      <div class="system-info-build">
        <h5>ALPHA Copy,</h5>
        <h5>Not all features may be avalible.</h5>
        <h5>Build <%=build %></h5>
      </div>
